name: Stock
title: Stock

api_list.name: Stocks List
api_list.description: You can get all list of our supported stocks names, ids, short name and country name.

optional_parameters.name: indices_id
optional_parameters.description:
When you need all stocks or all component from specific indices. Set indices_id={indices_id} in URL parameter.

**Default:** none
**Values:** 1,2,3... etc
**Note:** If the **"Country"** parameter exists in URL than the **"indices"** parameter will be ignored.

optional_parameters.name: sector
optional_parameters.description:
You can filter your stocks list by sector. Accept multi values with "," comma-separated.

**Default:** none
**Valid Values:** services... etc

optional_parameters.name: exchange
optional_parameters.description:
You can filter your stocks list by exchange. Accept multiple value with comma-separated.

**Default:** none
**Values:** nyse,nasdaq,paris... etc,
**Note:** Apple stock is available on multiple exchanges (Nasdaq,mexico, turkey, switzerland) and you want prices from nasdaq and mexico. so use symbol with exchange parameter.

optional_parameters.name: country
optional_parameters.description:
It is required when you use "All Stocks list" API, so you will get all stock from your selected country. Support 30 Countries

**Default:** none
**Valid Values:**
    brazil, canada, china,
    denmark, ~~dubai~~, finland, france,
    germany, hong-kong,
    india, indonesia, ireland,
    japan, malaysia, mexico, netherlands,
    pakistan, philippines, russia,
    saudi-arabia, singapore, south-africa, south-korea, spain, sweden, switzerland,
    thailand, turkey, united-arab-emirates, united-kingdom, united-states,

**Note:** You can set 1 or more country names to get all stocks from multiple countries by comma-separated names.

optional_parameters.name: output
optional_parameters.description:
Set your API response format.

**Default:** JSON
**Valid Values:** JSON, JSONP, object, XML, serialize and array
